rooms.Name: Out in the bay off the southern tip of Cinnabar Island
rooms.Description:
As you set sail on the bay, the wind whips up your hair and a smile comes
across your face as you think about the adventures that lie ahead.  The deep,
blue water gently rocks your boat and through the fog you can just make out
Cinnabar Island.  After double-checking your gear, you figure you're ready
for come serious Poke'mon collecting.

rooms.Name: Middle of the bay, south of Cinnabar Island
rooms.Description:
Looking off to the Northeast from here you can just make out the tops of the
Seafoam Islands.  The water here is deep, making it difficult to tell whether
there are any monsters swimming in the area.  Suddenly, a splash creates a
wave that breaks over the side of your boat.  Was that a Magikarp?

rooms.Name: The shallow water off Cinnabar Island
rooms.Description:
Finally, the sandy shoreline of Cinnabar Island comes into view.  Along the
shoreline you can see a half-dozen homes at the base of the mountain that
takes up most of the island.  With a million eager questions flying through
your mind, you are ready to storm the beach like an invading army.

rooms.Name: Cinnabar Island
rooms.Description:
You're eager to get started collecting Poke'mon but who could pass up a trip
to the genetic research lab.  Maybe you can get in line early and be the
first one to get in there.  That'll give you just the edge you need to defeat
a few Supernerds.  Maybe you can do a little experimenting of your own.

rooms.Name: Among the shorline homes of Cinnabar Island
rooms.Description:
Ahhhh Cinnabar Island.  This is where it all happens.  Cinnabar is home of
the famous genetics research lab where they created Mewtwo.  At the moment,
the town is over run with psychic Poke'mon and tourists.  With all these
tourists around, there's probably no chance of getting close to any rare
Poke'mon.

rooms.Name: Among the shorline homes of Cinnabar Island
rooms.Description:
Theres a beautiful view here off the North side of the Island.  Looking North
out on the bay the Sun is glistening off the small waves and a slight wind is
blowing light mist on you.  You can clearly see a town across the water to
the North.  That must be Pallet Town!

rooms.Name: Cinnabar Island
rooms.Description:
These tourists are getting rather annoying.  It's still early and maybe they
haven't invaded the other towns.  Wishful thinking.  This place is teaming
with tourists during the visitor season.  You're here aren't you?  It must be
100 degrees here on Cinnabar but to the east toward the Seafoam Islands there
appears to be ice in the water. Go figure.

rooms.Name: The bay towards the Seafoam Islands
rooms.Description:
The temperature has suddenly dropped to sub-zero and the wind is bitter cold.
Your boat is bumping against chunks of ice in the water.  Overhead, swarms of
birds are soaring and calling.  The Seafoam Islands are due East.  Wouldn't
it be nice to catch a glimpse of one of the legendary bird trio?

rooms.Name: The bay towards the Seafoam Islands
rooms.Description:
The temperature has suddenly dropped to sub-zero and the wind is bitter cold.
Your boat is bumping against chunks of ice in the water.  Overhead, swarms of
birds are soaring and calling.  The Seafoam Islands are just ahead.  The
shore is steep.  Pick your landing spot carefully

rooms.Name: The bay between Cinnabar Island and Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
The hometown for new trainers and rivals, Pallet Town, comes into full view.
Now's your chance to finally see Professor Oak's house. Just leave all those
freshly caught Poke'mon in the boat, this place seems like a low crime area.

rooms.Name: The bay between Cinnabar Island and Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
The water here is thriving with Water element Poke'mon.  Throw out the anchor
and grab your tackle.  What could be better? Looks like you've beat the
crowd.  There isn't a rival trainer or tourist in sight.

rooms.Name: The bay between Cinnabar Island and Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
The water here is thriving with Water element Poke'mon.  Throw out the anchor
and grab your tackle.  What could be better? Looks like you've beat the
crowd.  There isn't a rival trainer or tourist in sight.

rooms.Name: The bay between Cinnabar Island and Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
Still somewhat distracted by what you've seen at Cinnabar Island, you try and
shake it off and refocus on your mission.  The water here is thriving with
Water element Poke'mon.  Throw out the anchor and grab your tackle.  A few
quick catches is just the ticket to brighten things up.

rooms.Name: West Seafoam Island
rooms.Description:
The Seafoam Islands are worth a stop and look around.  It's the only place
you're gonna find Krabby, Kingler, and Articuno, if you're lucky.  And if you
find those crablegs are to your liking, check out the bay off Fuchsia City
for further seafood cuisine.

rooms.Name: East Seafoam Island
rooms.Description:
The Seafoam Islands are worth a stop and look around.  It's the only place
you're gonna find Krabby, Kingler, and Articuno, if you're lucky.  And if you
find those crablegs are to your liking, check out the bay off Fuchsia City
for further seafood cuisine.

rooms.Name: The bay area off the coast of Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:
The waters in the bay are overflowing with Water element Poke'mon. It's a
great day for sailing and an even greater day for fishing. You'll be patching
many holes in your monster collection on this outting.  There are Seels,
Magikarps, and Horseas as far as the eye can see.  Hope you brought a boat
load of Poke' Balls.

rooms.Name: The bay area off the coast of Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:
The waters in the bay are overflowing with Water element Poke'mon. It's a
great day for sailing and an even greater day for fishing. You'll be patching
many holes in your monster collection on this outting.  There are Seels,
Magikarps, and Horseas as far as the eye can see.  Hope you brought a boat
load of Poke' Balls.

rooms.Description:

great day for sailing and an even greater day for fishing. You'll be patching

load of Poke' Balls.

rooms.Name: Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:
Here in the streets of Fuchsia City, Poke'mon of all types run amuck both
playing and fighting.  Bulbasaur, Venusaur, Ivysaur, Sandslash, and more are
all here ready for a friendly? battle. When you've gotten your fill of
fighting, be sure to visit the park east of town.

rooms.Name: Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:

rooms.Name: Fuchsia City Bay Bridge
rooms.Description:
From here on the bridge, there is a spectacular view in all directions.  To
the North you can see a great view of Celadon City with Mt. Moon in the
background.  To the south you can see the Seafoam Islands.  Pallet town is to
the West and Fuchsia City to the East.  To the Northeast you can clearly see
the docks of Vermilion City with a cruise ship out anchored offshore.

rooms.Name: Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:
Here in the streets of Fuchsia City, Poke'mon of all types run amuck both
playing and fighting.  Bulbasaur, Venusaur, Ivysaur, Sandslash, and more are
all here ready for a friendly? battle. When you've gotten your fill of
fighting, be sure to visit the park east of town.

rooms.Name: Fuchsia City Square
rooms.Description:
Here in the town Square of Fuchsia City is a Poke'mon Center, where Poke'mon
can recover after each battle.  You can also log onto one of the many
computers here to check in with Professor Oak in order to see how you're
doing compared to other trainers, and store your Poke'mon in a special
storage system.

rooms.Name: Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:

rooms.Name: A path through the Celadon City Forest
rooms.Description:
Finally, you might have some luck getting a few bug and grass element
Poke'mon to add to your resume.  Seems the other trainers have been scarfing
them up and leaving you with none.  Keep an eye out for a stray Oddish,
Gloom, Paras or Vileplume.

rooms.Name: The bay area off the coast of Fuchsia City

rooms.Name: Southern edge of Celadon City
rooms.Description:
Standing here on the edge of Celadon City, you recall the stories you've
heard in the other towns about the fierce fighters that roam these streets.
Shaking off those tall tales and dismissing them as pure myth, it's time to
find a Poke'mon Center and store these newly caught monsters.

rooms.Name: The streets of Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
So much to do and so little time.  Professor Oak must be around here
somewhere.  Though, he's probably trying to avoid these crowds. You hope
something truly exciting happens on this trip so you don't have to make up
lies about your vacation like last year's trip to Six Flags.

rooms.Name: The streets of Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
Everything here is town is a little crispy and charred.  The Pallet Town fire
department must be exhausted.  All these low level Poke'mon are cute for the
tourists and clumsy new trainers.  But, you crave the big dogs. Keep moving.
This whole place can't be a kiddie park can it?

rooms.Name: Pallet Town Square
rooms.Description:
Here in the center of Pallet Town is a beautiful steaming fountain.  It must
have cost a small fortune to build.  You find it somewhat disappointing that
this place is so commercialized.  You have a strong urge to kill all these
camera happy vacationers.  Perhaps, you can get your picture taken by the
fountain first.

rooms.Name: The streets of Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
Pallet Town sits on the South edge of the mainland and is dotted with average
looking small homes.  Currently the town is nearly taken over with Fire
element Poke'mon and tourists.  Probably a bad thing for most tourists.  But
for a skilled hunter like you, it's a gift from heaven and an opportunity of
a lifetime.

rooms.Name: The streets of Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
Oh sheesh, is this place ever crowded.  Seemed like a good idea but you were
nowhere near being the first person to think so.  Maybe just skip Pallet Town
and head on up to Veridian City.  Hold up.  Is that a Charizard?

rooms.Name: The streets of Pallet Town
rooms.Description:
Having gotten yourself a few new low level Poke'mon to add to your growing
collection, it's time to move on.  Across the grassy clearing to the
Northwest, is the outline of a small town.  Give yourself a little reassuring
pep talk and get going.

rooms.Name: The rolling hills of Southern Viridian
rooms.Description:
Seems surprising that this perfectly landscaped field is vacant. You'd think
it to be Poke'mon paradise.  With a gorgeous view of the bay to the west and
the Celadon forest as a backdrop to the east, you may want to stop and let
some of your Poke'mon out of their Poke' Balls for a bit.

rooms.Name: The rolling hills of Southern Viridian
rooms.Description:
Seems surprising that this perfectly landscaped field is vacant. You'd think
it to be Poke'mon paradise.  A rival trainer has definitely beat you to the
goodies.  Can't let this happen all day.  Pick up the pace!

rooms.Name: Viridian City
rooms.Description:
Arriving in Veridian City, you notice the place is crawling with poisonous
Poke'mon.  Better check your supply of antidote or perhaps there's a Poke'
Mart around here somewhere.

rooms.Name: Viridian City
rooms.Description:
Most of the side streets here in town are barricaded.  Looks like they're
getting ready for a parade.  The sidewalks are lined with spectators. You
notice a trainer carefully handling a Venonant and about bust a gut laughing
as he gets bitten and starts to cry.  Sucker.

rooms.Name: Viridian City
rooms.Description:
Running low on antidote? Good news is there's a Poke' Mart right here. Bad
news is its closed.  Be careful with these posionous monsters. One wrong move
and this vacation will be all over, just like the time you stepped on that
starfish in Florida.

rooms.Name: Viridian City
rooms.Description:
Trying to sort through all these posionous Poke'mon is tricky.  Hope you
brought a list of them all because this is getting complicated. Got a Weedle,
Nidoran male and female, Beedrill, Venonat, and what's the name of that other
one.....?

rooms.Name: Viridian City
rooms.Description:
The road splits here at the North end of town.  A sign with an arrow points
Northeast and reads "To Pewter City".  Another sign points west and reads "to
Indigo Plateau".

rooms.Name: Viridian City
rooms.Description:
You stop here in a quiet spot on the edge of the city.  You've heard rumors
that Mewtwo is somewhere up on Mt. Moon after escaping the Lab on Cinnabar
Island.  It would be awsome to go on over there and scout around for Mewtwo,
but you're too young to die, so a better plan would be to spend some time at
Indigo Plateau gathering a little more experience.

rooms.Name: The path to Indigo Plateau
rooms.Description:
The wooded path to Indigo Plateau would be an ideal spot for capturing some
bug and grass element Poke'mon.  And a few minutes ago you could have.  Some
rival trainers in desperate need of them are a few steps ahead of you today
and the area is picked clean.

rooms.Name: The path to Indigo Plateau
rooms.Description:
The wooded path to Indigo Plateau would be an ideal spot for capturing some
bug and grass element Poke'mon.  And a few minutes ago you could have.  Some
rival trainers in desperate need of them are a few steps ahead of you today
and the area is picked clean.

rooms.Name: The path to Indigo Plateau
rooms.Description:
The wooded path to Indigo Plateau would be an ideal spot for capturing some
bug and grass element Poke'mon.  And a few minutes ago you could have.  Some
rival trainers in desperate need of them are a few steps ahead of you today
and the area is picked clean.

rooms.Name: The entrance to Indigo Plateau
rooms.Description:
Standing here at the edge of the famous Plateau, the excitement boils your
blood.  Many legendary trainers have made and lost reputations on this very
soil.  Today, you'll get the same chance they had.  Ancient pillars line the
walkway and you can almost feel the electric energy in the air.

rooms.Name: Indigo Plateau
rooms.Description:
The towns and cities are where all the action is and Indigo Plateau is no
exception.  The electric element Poke'mon here are constantly engaging in
battles.  They come here attracted by the energy of the powerplant.  Often
this creates havoc for the towns.  The intense battles here sometimes cause
power outages.  It's rumored that professor Oak himself can occasionally be
found here spying on the new trainers to check on their progress.

rooms.Name: Indigo Plateau Power Plant
rooms.Description:
The power plant was rumored to be over on the east bay, but here it is at
Indigo Plateau.  Heh, don't believe everything you read on the internet.
Professor Oak is here peeking out one of the side entrances.  He's checking
up on a new trainer. As you rush up on him like an over-eager puppy, you
nearly trip on a trapdoor on the floor.

Exits.Description: Team Rocket wishes you hadn't noticed this door!

rooms.Name: Secret tunnel to Team Rocket's Headquarters
rooms.Description:
Now this is getting better.  You've always wanted a chance to give that Team
Rocket a thrashing.  A grin comes over your face as you think about punting a
couple of field goals with that clepto cat, Meowth.  The tunnel smells
extremely foul from all the gross Poke'mon that Team Rocket stores down here.
Clinch your nose and grab a Poke' ball.  You can have a good laugh later when
Jesse and James find all their prize monsters missing.

Exits.Description: Finally, you found the way out of here.

rooms.Name: Secret tunnel to Team Rocket's Headquarters
rooms.Description:
The tunnel comes to an end here and the air down here is completely
unbearable.  As you prepare to give up your search and head back the way you
came in, a possible exit on the ceiling catches your eye.  Pausing quietly,
you can barely hear voices above you.

rooms.Name: The thick forest outside Pewter City
rooms.Description:
The wooded path to Pewter City would be yet another ideal spot for capturing
some bug and grass element Poke'mon.  However, those rival trainers must
still be in desperate need of them and are still a few steps ahead of you and
the area here is picked clean as well.

rooms.Name: The thick forest outside Pewter City
rooms.Description:

some bug and grass element Poke'mon.  However, those rival trainers must

the area here is picked clean as well.

rooms.Name: Southern edge of Pewter City
rooms.Description:
If your collection is lacking in the pheasant variety, then prepare to be
compensated.  Rumor has it that Pewter City is home to several foul species
of pocket monsters.

rooms.Name: Touring Pewter City
rooms.Description:
Pewter City has been invaded by birds and rats.  If you're in need of a
Pidgeot, Raticate, or Dodrio, you're in luck.  Back in Pallet Town there are
rumors that Team Rocket have a secret meeting place somewhere near Pewter
City.  Could be worth investigating. Looking to the Northeast, you can see
Mt. Moon against the horizon.

rooms.Name: Touring Pewter City
rooms.Description:

Pidgeot, Raticate, or Dodrio, you're in luck.  Back in Pallet Town there are

rooms.Name: Team Rocket's Headquarters
rooms.Description:
Rushing into the room, you've no doubt caught these losers off guard.  But,
too bad you weren't as prepared as you thought.  All those things you wanted
to say to these guys get stuck in your throat.  Hanging on the walls and
thrown about the room are sketched out plans and notes.  Before you can even
think about grabbing anything here, you're gonna have to kick some Team
Rocket butt.

rooms.Name: Pewter City Square
rooms.Description:
Here in the town Square of Pewter City is a Poke'mon Center, where Poke'mon
can recover after each battle.  You can also log onto one of the many
computers here to check in with Professor Oak in order to see how you're
doing compared to other trainers, and store your Poke'mon in a special
storage system.

rooms.Name: A path to Mt. Moon
rooms.Description:
Yes! Mt. Moon in full view.  Theres nothing between you and the summit of Mt.
Moon except this path and a few Supernerds. The Supergeeks won't be too happy
to see you getting close to the mountain and they challenge any new trainer
that wanders across this path.

rooms.Name: The base of Mt. Moon
rooms.Description:
Standing here at the base of Mt. Moon you realize the time is near for the
ultimate showdown between master and Poke'mon.  Mewtwo is somewhere here on
the Mountain and you're determined to find him. There's no direct path up the
steep sides, but there's a loose boulder here.  You just might be able to
wedge it open.

rooms.Name: A tunnel beneath Mt. Moon
rooms.Description:
This tunnel, although narrow, is crawling with Rock element Poke'mon .  While
you're looking for clues to the whereabouts of Mewtwo, you may as well bag a
few of these rare monsters.  If you're in need of a Dugtrio or a Clefairy,
you're in the right place.

Exits.Description: The psychic barrier is very strong, indeed.

rooms.Name: Top of Mt. Moon
rooms.Description:
Here at the top of Mt. Moon sits Mewtwo in a half-conscious state of
meditation.  You can look down and see all the towns, from Cinnabar Island to
Indigo Plateau to Lavender Town. Here armed with full confidence, having
kicked butt and taken names in all those towns, you are ready to take down
the big dog himself...errr big cat.  Aren't you?
